{/*

Uploading

 */}

You can upload files to your Google Drive account using the upload method.

The upload method accepts two parameters:

  • file - The file to upload
  • name - The name of the file

The upload method returns a promise that resolves to the uploaded file.

The following example uploads a file to your Google Drive account: 

                                        
                                            {`const file = new File(['Hello World'], 'hello.txt', {
    type: 'text/plain',
});

drive.upload(file, 'hello.txt')
    .then((file) => {
        console.log(file);
    });`}
); }
